<% content_for :title, "Terms of Service — Turf Totals" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Terms of Service for Turf Totals, the skill-based World Cup pick'em game. Eligibility, state availability, entries, payments, refunds, and the referral program." %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-10 px-2 space-y-12">
  <header>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-heading mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-secondary text-sm">Last updated <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %>.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      These Terms of Service govern your use of Turf Totals, a skill-based sports pick&rsquo;em game
      operated by McRitchie Studio (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo;). By creating an account or entering a
      contest you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the game.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Eligibility</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>
        You must be of legal age to participate in skill-based contests in your state:
        <strong>18+</strong> in most states, <strong>19+</strong> in Alabama and Nebraska, and
        <strong>21+</strong> in Iowa, Massachusetts, and Virginia. You attest to this when you
        create an account.
      </li>
      <li>
        Turf Totals is a game of <strong>skill</strong>, not chance. It is available only where
        skill-based contests are permitted — see the state eligibility section below. We use
        approximate location to enforce this; you may not use a VPN or other means to circumvent
        geo-eligibility.
      </li>
      <li>One account per person. Operating multiple accounts may result in suspension and forfeiture of entries.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="state-eligibility" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-24">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">State eligibility</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Paid contest entry is not available in the following U.S. states. This list is rendered
      from the same setting our IP-geolocation enforcement reads, and it may change as state law
      and guidance evolve:
    </p>
    <%= render "pages/excluded_states_list", excluded_states: @excluded_states %>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Eligibility is enforced by IP geolocation when you enter a contest or move funds. See the
      <%= link_to "State Eligibility page", state_eligibility_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
      for details.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">How contests work</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>Each contest presents a slate of team matchups. You select six to form an entry.</li>
      <li>Each pick is scored as the team&rsquo;s goals scored multiplied by its Turf Score; your entry score is the sum.</li>
      <li>Entries are ranked highest score first, and prizes are paid per the published payout table for that contest.</li>
      <li>
        Once a contest locks (at its published lock time, enforced on-chain), entries can no longer
        be submitted or changed. Settlement occurs after the relevant real-world matches conclude.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Payments, entry fees, and payouts</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>
        Entry fees and prizes are <strong>denominated in U.S. dollars</strong> and settled in
        <strong>USDC</strong>, a fully-reserved U.S. dollar stablecoin, on the Solana blockchain.
        A $500 prize is $500 &mdash; settlement in USDC determines how it is delivered, not how
        much it is worth.
      </li>
      <li>
        If you pay from your own wallet, your funds remain there until you enter a contest;
        entering transfers exactly the entry fee and nothing more. We do not request token
        approvals, spending delegation, or custody of an open-ended balance.
      </li>
      <li>
        Contest-entry credits (entry tokens) may be purchased by card. Each credit redeems for
        one contest entry. Card data is handled by our payment processor under its own secure
        systems &mdash; we never see your full card number.
      </li>
      <li>
        Prize payouts are released from a per-contest prize-pool account secured by a 2-of-3
        multisig. No single key can move prize funds.
      </li>
      <li>
        All blockchain transactions are final and irreversible once confirmed. Network fees and
        third-party payment-processing fees are non-refundable.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="refunds" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-24">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Refunds and cancellations</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Cancelled contests.</strong> If a contest is cancelled before it locks, entry
        fees are refunded in the form you paid, within <strong>7 days</strong> of cancellation:
        entries paid with a purchased entry credit have the credit restored (or, on request,
        refunded to your original payment method), and entry fees paid in USDC from your wallet
        are returned in USDC. Contact
        <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">alex@turfmonster.media</a>
        and we will process it within that window.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Editing your entry.</strong> While a Turf Totals contest is open you can change
        the picks on a submitted entry from the contest page (picks whose real-world games have
        already kicked off cannot be changed, and Survivor entries do not support editing). Once
        a contest locks, entries are final: fees have entered the prize pool and cannot be
        withdrawn or refunded.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Unused entry credits.</strong> Purchased entry-token credits that you have not
        redeemed for a contest entry are refundable on request to your original payment method
        &mdash; contact support and we will process the refund within 7 days.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>On-chain finality.</strong> Confirmed blockchain transactions are final and
        irreversible; network fees and third-party payment-processing fees are non-refundable in
        all cases.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Card disputes.</strong> Before disputing a charge with your card issuer, please
        contact
        <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">alex@turfmonster.media</a>
        &mdash; nearly every issue is resolved faster by support. Charges appear on your
        statement under the descriptor <strong>TURF MONSTER</strong>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>Do not cheat, collude, exploit bugs, or use automated agents to gain an unfair advantage.</li>
      <li>Do not attempt to access other users&rsquo; accounts or interfere with the game&rsquo;s operation.</li>
      <li>We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms, and void affected entries.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="referrals" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-24">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Referral Program</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Every account has a personal referral link of the form
      <code class="text-xs bg-inset px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">.../contests/:slug?ref=&lt;your-slug&gt;</code>.
      Share it from any contest page using the &ldquo;Bring &nbsp;✌️ Friends, Get a Free Entry&rdquo;
      card and you&rsquo;ll earn free contest entries when your invites convert.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading">How a referral is recorded</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li>When a visitor lands on <em>any</em> Turf Totals page with a <code class="text-xs bg-inset px-1 rounded">?ref=</code> parameter, the referrer slug is saved in the visitor&rsquo;s browser before the URL is cleaned up.</li>
      <li>The referrer is locked in the moment they sign up <em>or</em> log in for the first time after clicking. After that, the link is associated with their account permanently and cannot be changed.</li>
      <li>If a visitor already has an account, the referrer is recorded only if they don&rsquo;t already have one.</li>
      <li>Self-referrals are rejected.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading">How a free entry is earned</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li>A free entry is credited to the referrer when <strong>two distinct invitees</strong> each sign up <em>and</em> submit a paid contest entry of their own.</li>
      <li>Sign-ups alone do not qualify. The invitee must complete an entry; carts and abandoned entries don&rsquo;t count.</li>
      <li>Referrals stack: every two qualifying invitees earns one free entry. Four qualifying invitees earns two, and so on.</li>
      <li>Free entries are credited as Entry Tokens (see your <%= link_to "Account page", account_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>) and may be redeemed in any open contest they cover.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading">Eligibility &amp; abuse</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li>Inviter and invitee must be different real users. Multiple accounts controlled by the same person disqualify the referral chain and may result in account freezes.</li>
      <li>Turf Totals reserves the right to void referrals, revoke earned free entries, or freeze accounts that abuse the program.</li>
      <li>The program may change or end at any time; entries already earned will be honored.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Disclaimers and limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      The game is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; without warranties of any kind. Blockchain networks,
      wallet software, and third-party providers are outside our control and may experience
      delays, congestion, or outages. To the fullest extent permitted by law, our liability for
      any claim arising from your use of Turf Totals is limited to the entry fees you paid for the
      contest giving rise to the claim.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We may update these terms as the product evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the
      &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above. Continued use after a change constitutes acceptance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-2 text-sm text-secondary border-t border-subtle pt-6">
    <p>
      Questions? Email
      <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">alex@turfmonster.media</a>.
      See also our
      <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>,
      <%= link_to "Responsible Gaming", responsible_gaming_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>,
      <%= link_to "State Eligibility", state_eligibility_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>,
      and
      <%= link_to "About page", about_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
